==English==

===Etymology===
Late Latin ''[[cordialis]]'', from Latin ''[[cor]]'' heart; French ''cordial''.

===Adjective===
'''cordial''' ([[cordially]])
#Hearty; sincere; warm; affectionate.
#Tending to revive, cheer, or invigorate; giving strength or spirits.

====Synonyms====
*[[hearty]]
*[[sincere]]
*[[heartfelt]]
*[[warm]]
*[[affectionate]]
*[[cheer]]ing
*[[invigorating]]

====Translations====
;hearty
*Swedish: [[hjärtlig]]
;reviving


===Noun===
'''cordial''' (plural: ''cordials'')
# A [[candy]] (or [[bonbon]]) usually made of milk [[chocolate]], filled with small fruits (often maraschino [[cherry|cherries]]) and syrup or [[fondant]].
# A [[liqueur]] prepared using the infusion process.
#''(UK & Australia)'': A (usually entirely artificial) concentrated noncarbonated soft drink which is diluted with water before drinking, said to have some medicinal properties.

====Related Terms====
*[[liqueur]] (1)
*[[cognac]] (2)

===Related terms===
*[[cordiality]]
*[[cordially]]

